CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 3, 1954, pg. 32 reads: "Orbin Street Block Club -This group, the first to organize in the Vann School District, plans to try to convert a vacant lot in that district into a playground.  Robert Ruffin, Hill City supervisor of block clubs, center, last week, met with officers of the group.  They include, left to right, Mrs. Rubell Barnes, social chairman; Mrs. Josephine Scott, secretary; Mr. Ruffin, Mrs. Carrie Foster, president; Mrs. Winnie Lesesne, treasurer, and Mrs. Rosetta Stewart, vice president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Orbin Street Block Club members, from left: Rubell Barnes, Josephine Scott, Carrie Foster, Winnie Lesesne, and Rosetta Stewart, meeting with Robert Ruffin gathered in domestic interior with light colored walls, sofa, coffee table, and military portraits, another version
